Introduction
This project provides visual insights into deforestation trends in the Amazon and Pantanal regions from 2004 to 2023. The visualizations include line charts, bar graphs, 3D scatter plots, and interactive graphs created using Python libraries Matplotlib and Plotly.

Data Sources
The data used in this project is based on fictional values derived from the text provided and historical trends from the National Institute for Space Research (INPE).
